title: Some games and genres
author: Justin

<p>For CS 399 - Game Design, we're looking at genres, types of games, and audiences. Here are <em>some</em> <em>relatively</em> concrete video game genres and the games I most associate with each:</p><dl><dt>Adventure</dt>	<dd>Monkey Island series (PC), Myst series (PC)</dd><dt>Role Playing</dt>	<dd>Final Fantasy (NES, PS, PS2)</dd><dt>1st Person Shooter</dt>	<dd>Quake series, Unreal series, Descent series [all PC]</dd><dt>3rd Person Shooter</dt>	<dd>MDK (PC)</dd><dt>Real Time Strategy</dt>	<dd> Starcraft , Homeworld, Shogun [all PC]</dd><dt>God Game</dt>	<dd> SimCity, Black &amp; White [all PC]</dd><dt>MMORPG</dt>	<dd> World Of Warcraft (PC)</dd><dt>Edutainment</dt>	<dd>?</dd><dt>Fighting</dt>	<dd>Soul Calibur 2 (PS2, GC), Tekken series (PS), Mortal Kombat (consoles, PC)</dd><dt>Game Simulation</dt>	<dd>?</dd><dt>Driving Simulation</dt>	<dd>Gran Tourismo (PS)</dd><dt>Sports</dt>	<dd> Madden NFL, Winning Eleven [consoles]</dd><dt>Puzzle</dt>	<dd> Tetris (myriad consoles, PC), Bejeweled (PC)</dd><dt>Music</dt>	<dd> Rez (PS), DDR (PS), Global Defense Network (PC)</dd><dt>Kids</dt>	<dd>?</dd><dt>Platformer</dt>	<dd>Super Mario Sunshine (GC), Crash Bandicoot (PS, GC), Tomb Raider (PC)</dd></dl><p>If you have any suggestions, email me with them, or if you're in the class, email me for an edit password.</p>